{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/theimpossibleastronaut/awesome-linguistics/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"cb863c00-e80f-508a-9695-0ef63f060e69","html":"<h3 id=\"awesome-linguistics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-linguistics\" aria-label=\"awesome linguistics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Linguistics</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></p>\n<p>A curated list of anything remotely related to linguistics, sorted in alphabetical order.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#programming\">Programming</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#platforms-and-toolkits\">Platforms and toolkits</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#algorithms\">Algorithms</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#data-sets\">Data sets</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#resources\">Resources</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#on-wikipedia\">On Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#books\">Books</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#free\">Free</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#non-free\">Non free</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#lists\">Lists</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"programming\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#programming\" aria-label=\"programming permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Programming</h3>\n<p><em>Libraries, frameworks and applications useful for developing applications.</em></p>\n<h3 id=\"platforms-and-toolkits\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#platforms-and-toolkits\" aria-label=\"platforms and toolkits permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Platforms and toolkits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sexybiggetje/haxe-linguistics\">Haxe-linguistics</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sexybiggetje/haxe-linguistics\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">25</span></span></a> - Early linguistical analysis and natural language processing library for Haxe.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/NaturalNode/natural\">Natural</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/NaturalNode/natural\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9.6k</span></span></a> - General natural language tools for Node.js.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.nltk.org/\">Natural Language ToolKit (NLTK)</a> - The most complete platform for building Python programs to work with human language data.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://snowball.tartarus.org/\">Snowball</a> - Snowball is a language in which stemming algorithms can be easily represented.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://spacy.io/\">Spacy</a> - Industrial-strength  National Language Processing in Python.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mikahama/uralicNLP\">UralicNLP</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mikahama/uralicNLP\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">34</span></span></a> - An open source Python library for processing morphologically rich and, for the most part, endangered Uralic languages. It can do morphological analysis, generation, lemmatization, disambiguation and lexical lookup for a great many Uralic languages.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"algorithms\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#algorithms\" aria-label=\"algorithms permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Algorithms</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://snowball.tartarus.org/texts/stemmersoverview.html\">Stemming algorithms for various European languages</a> - Various stemming algorithms from snowball.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://tartarus.org/martin/PorterStemmer/\">The Porter Stemmer Algorithm</a> - The ‘official’ home page for distribution of the Porter Stemming Algorithm, written and maintained by its author, Martin Porter.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"data-sets\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#data-sets\" aria-label=\"data sets permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Data sets</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kirkins/euroromcom\">EuroRomCom Data</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kirkins/euroromcom\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a> - JSON formatted Pan-Romance word lists.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lighttag.io/how-to-label-data/\">How To Label Data</a> - Guide on managing large scale linguistic annotation projects.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RIchardLitt/low-resource-languages\">Low Resource Languages</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/RIchardLitt/low-resource-languages\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">251</span></span></a> - A list of resources for conservation, development, and documentation of low resource (human) languages.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"on-wikipedia\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#on-wikipedia\" aria-label=\"on wikipedia permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>On Wikipedia</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag-of-words_model\">Bag of words model</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Document_classification\">Document classification</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_model\">Language models</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naive_Bayes_classifier\">Naive Bayes classification</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_language_processing\">Natural language processing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outline_of_natural_language_processing\">Outline of natural language processing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Part-of-speech_tagging\">Parts of speech tagging</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sentiment_analysis\">Sentiment analysis</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tf%E2%80%93idf\">Term frequency - inverse document frequency</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vector_space_model\">Vector space model</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"on-youtube\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#on-youtube\" aria-label=\"on youtube permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>On Youtube</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLegWUnz91WfuPebLI97-WueAP90JO-15i\">Computational Linguistics Lecture Playlist (Youtube)</a> - Lectures for University of Maryland class on computational linguistics.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCaMpov1PPVXGcKYgwHjXB3g\">The Virtual Linguistics Campus</a> - CC-licensed educational videos interconnected with Marburg University's e-learning platform of the same name.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"books\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#books\" aria-label=\"books permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Books</h3>\n<p><em>Some of the more interesting and complete books.</em></p>\n<h4 id=\"free\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#free\" aria-label=\"free permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-